<p class="">The hon. Gentleman began his speech by reaching a conclusion. Later on, he asked that information should be given on the basis of which he could reach a conclusion. He cannot have it both ways, and he ought not to prejudge the issue if he really wants the facts.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
